WEBVTT

00:00:00.935 --> 00:00:02.469
[♪ "Red Right Hand" playing]

00:00:05.138 --> 00:00:10.344
♪ Take a little walk To the edge
of town And go across the tracks ♪

00:00:10.477 --> 00:00:12.037
[teenager 1] Where do I have to put it?

00:00:12.847 --> 00:00:19.954
♪ Where the viaduct looms like A
bird of doom As it shifts and cracks ♪

00:00:21.288 --> 00:00:23.457
♪ Where secrets lie ♪

00:00:23.625 --> 00:00:27.294
♪ In the border fires
In the humming wires ♪

00:00:27.427 --> 00:00:32.499
Anywhere you want as long as
the pumpkin touches the porch.

00:00:34.802 --> 00:00:37.137
[stammers] Maybe
we should just go to the party.

00:00:37.271 --> 00:00:39.807
Come on, show some backbone.
We've both done it.

00:00:39.974 --> 00:00:40.974
[sighs]

00:00:41.009 --> 00:00:42.442
♪ His catastrophic plan ♪

00:00:42.544 --> 00:00:46.648
♪ Designed and directed
By his red right hand ♪

00:00:54.656 --> 00:00:55.657
Yes!

00:00:55.790 --> 00:00:57.057
Yes.

00:00:57.825 --> 00:00:59.159
[screaming]

00:00:59.326 --> 00:01:00.562
Come on.

00:01:00.695 --> 00:01:01.996
[screaming continues]

00:01:04.498 --> 00:01:05.533
[grunts]

00:01:09.671 --> 00:01:10.672
[gasps]

00:01:15.342 --> 00:01:16.711
What's she doing to him?

00:01:17.845 --> 00:01:19.514
[teenagers scream]

00:01:21.000 --> 00:01:27.074
- Do you want subtitles for any video?
- =[ ai.Open Subtitles.com ]=

00:01:39.701 --> 00:01:41.461
- [Elliot] Mom.
- [gasps] What? Are you okay?

00:01:41.536 --> 00:01:43.403
- Guess who I am?
- Uh...

00:01:43.538 --> 00:01:45.105
A sassy friar?

00:01:45.238 --> 00:01:46.541
Hang on.

00:01:47.207 --> 00:01:50.087
Dad ordered this for me on Prime to
be sure it got here before Halloween.

00:01:52.714 --> 00:01:56.383
- How about now?
- Okay, uh... a science friar.

00:01:56.517 --> 00:01:58.251
I'm Copernicus.

00:01:58.418 --> 00:02:00.396
He was the first one to realize the
sun is at the center of the solar system.

00:02:00.420 --> 00:02:03.457
Oh, yeah. Okay. Yeah, I see it. I love it.

00:02:03.591 --> 00:02:04.892
What time is it?

00:02:05.392 --> 00:02:07.227
Jeez, I fell asleep, huh?

00:02:07.361 --> 00:02:08.563
What's that?

00:02:08.730 --> 00:02:09.897
Well, this is...

00:02:11.065 --> 00:02:12.967
Let's just say it's the reason

00:02:13.101 --> 00:02:14.878
your sister and I aren't
exactly talking right now.

00:02:14.902 --> 00:02:16.412
What's she doing? Is she still up too?

00:02:16.436 --> 00:02:18.706
She's barely come out of her
room since you grounded her.

00:02:19.139 --> 00:02:20.979
- I think you should talk to her.
- Oh, you do?

00:02:21.109 --> 00:02:22.629
Okay, well, thank you for your advice,

00:02:22.744 --> 00:02:25.046
but I think I'm going to Aristotle this one.

00:02:26.114 --> 00:02:28.950
Aristotle. He thought silence
was louder than yelling.

00:02:29.584 --> 00:02:31.451
Close enough.

00:02:31.619 --> 00:02:34.064
Yes, but Aristotle also believed anger
must always be within the golden mean,

00:02:34.088 --> 00:02:36.557
not excessive, at the right
time for the right purpose.

00:02:36.658 --> 00:02:37.959
Dead on, kid.

00:02:38.793 --> 00:02:40.873
All right, fine. I'm gonna
talk to her at some point.

00:02:40.928 --> 00:02:42.764
- [phone buzzes]
- Don't worry about it.

00:02:43.564 --> 00:02:45.800
Oh, I got a work thing I gotta go to.

00:02:45.933 --> 00:02:48.173
- You go to bed. Why are you still even up?
- Yeah. Okay.

00:02:48.268 --> 00:02:50.270
Go. I love the costume.

00:02:57.512 --> 00:02:59.781
[police radio chatter]

00:02:59.947 --> 00:03:01.683
[creaking]

00:03:01.816 --> 00:03:04.284
[wind whistling]

00:03:05.185 --> 00:03:06.988
[clock clicking, gongs]

00:03:07.121 --> 00:03:09.824
[clock ticking]

00:03:09.957 --> 00:03:11.159
[gongs]

00:03:13.995 --> 00:03:15.129
[camera shutter clicks]

00:03:15.295 --> 00:03:19.000
This is perfect. It's our
first Halloween together.

00:03:19.133 --> 00:03:20.501
- Is it?
- Yeah.

00:03:20.635 --> 00:03:21.836
Hop on in here, buddy.

00:03:23.336 --> 00:03:24.939
I'm not eating candy at a crime scene.

00:03:25.039 --> 00:03:26.841
Right, right. Why have fun?

00:03:27.474 --> 00:03:29.620
I would've thought Halloween
was your favorite holiday.

00:03:29.644 --> 00:03:31.789
- Why would you think that?
- It's like the one day of the year

00:03:31.813 --> 00:03:34.182
you can let your hair down,
throw a costume on,

00:03:34.314 --> 00:03:37.484
be somebody other than you
for one night.

00:03:37.652 --> 00:03:38.653
[doorbell rings]

00:03:39.352 --> 00:03:40.387
Trick or treat!

00:03:41.656 --> 00:03:42.957
Okay, I was wrong.

00:03:43.057 --> 00:03:45.177
- Can we focus on our dead man?
- Yeah, let's do that.

00:03:47.195 --> 00:03:48.863
This is Danny Sternblatt.

00:03:48.996 --> 00:03:51.199
Divorce lawyer
to the 1%, including the mayor

00:03:51.331 --> 00:03:53.233
when he split from his wife last year.

00:03:53.366 --> 00:03:54.736
What happened to the walls?

00:03:54.869 --> 00:03:57.114
Who killed the lights? The
electricity is on in the block.

00:03:57.138 --> 00:03:59.339
Says the motion-sensor werewolf
across the street.

00:04:01.676 --> 00:04:03.410
[screams] Down! No!

00:04:03.544 --> 00:04:04.746
He knows.

00:04:04.879 --> 00:04:06.914
The power's cut at
the main panel, as in severed.

00:04:07.048 --> 00:04:09.016
I'm not sure yet by whom
or who went at the walls.

00:04:09.550 --> 00:04:11.552
Also, the, uh, 911 call was unusual.

00:04:11.719 --> 00:04:13.997
A group of teens said that they
heard a scream through the window

00:04:14.021 --> 00:04:16.356
and claimed to see something
white and flowy attack him.

00:04:17.225 --> 00:04:19.093
White and flowy? Come on.

00:04:19.227 --> 00:04:21.071
As far as I'm concerned,
it could've been the curtains.

00:04:21.095 --> 00:04:22.395
Yeah, or their imaginations.

00:04:22.530 --> 00:04:24.410
Could be Sternblatt just
died of natural causes,

00:04:24.532 --> 00:04:27.343
- which is part of what we're here to find out.
- He's got marks on his arm.

00:04:27.367 --> 00:04:29.170
Looks like somebody
grabbed him real hard.

00:04:29.269 --> 00:04:31.589
Or Danny grabbed his own arm,
maybe during a medical event?

00:04:31.706 --> 00:04:35.109
Perhaps a heart attack, shooting
pain down the arm, certainly a symptom.

00:04:35.243 --> 00:04:38.345
Uh-huh. His hair is either
falling out or he is pulling it out.

00:04:38.445 --> 00:04:40.748
That with the dark bags under his eyes,

00:04:40.882 --> 00:04:42.562
I don't think
Danny was sleeping very well.

00:04:42.717 --> 00:04:43.718
[Karadec] Mmm.

00:04:48.589 --> 00:04:50.224
Well, we know
who murdered the woodwork.

00:04:50.390 --> 00:04:53.426
These blisters on Danny's hands
say he was the vandal.

00:04:53.561 --> 00:04:56.130
Benzo's for sleep, which
clearly weren't working very well.

00:04:56.264 --> 00:04:58.984
And heart meds, nitroglycerin.
It's another point for natural causes.

00:05:00.433 --> 00:05:02.603
We're thinking he was
sitting over here working

00:05:02.737 --> 00:05:05.740
when his heart gave out, knocked
over his plate on his way down

00:05:05.873 --> 00:05:07.108
and ended up there.

00:05:07.909 --> 00:05:10.229
At least he won't have to read
his own handwriting anymore.

00:05:10.711 --> 00:05:12.122
Something doesn't
make sense here though.

00:05:12.146 --> 00:05:14.314
Imagine you're Danny.
He's having a heart attack.

00:05:14.447 --> 00:05:17.450
You know you have a bad heart. You
have lifesaving medication over there.

00:05:17.585 --> 00:05:19.587
Why would you
run away from the bathroom?

00:05:19.754 --> 00:05:21.674
He must've been going
towards something this way.

00:05:22.422 --> 00:05:23.423
That?

00:05:28.262 --> 00:05:31.098
Either obsidian or black tourmaline.

00:05:31.265 --> 00:05:33.601
- Why this?
- Maybe an ugly gift from a wife?

00:05:33.734 --> 00:05:35.854
Yeah, could be. Danny's
going through his own divorce.

00:05:35.970 --> 00:05:37.404
We contacted the wife, Lorraine.

00:05:37.505 --> 00:05:39.750
She's on business in London,
catching the first flight back.

00:05:39.774 --> 00:05:42.176
- So the white flowy thing, not a wife.
- Mmm.

00:05:42.310 --> 00:05:46.479
Depends which wife. Lorraine Sternblatt
or the ghost of Maddie St. Croix?

00:05:47.480 --> 00:05:49.116
Sorry, did you just say ghost?

00:05:49.250 --> 00:05:50.284
Mm-hmm.

00:05:51.719 --> 00:05:53.063
[Daphne] Oh, wait, just to be clear,

00:05:53.087 --> 00:05:55.790
I am not suggesting a ghost
killed Danny Sternblatt.

00:05:55.957 --> 00:05:57.592
You're not not suggesting it.

00:05:57.692 --> 00:06:00.962
I like true crime podcasts, sometimes
ghosts stories. No shame there.

00:06:01.128 --> 00:06:03.264
And the Spencer house,
where we are now, checks both.

00:06:03.363 --> 00:06:05.666
Have you heard of Dash Spencer
and Maddie St. Croix?

00:06:05.800 --> 00:06:09.670
1940s movie stars, screwball
comedies. Uh, mostly involved a monkey.

00:06:09.804 --> 00:06:11.539
Well, they were married in real life too.

00:06:11.672 --> 00:06:13.752
The it couple of their day,
and this was their house.

00:06:13.808 --> 00:06:16.143
Got that from Spencer house.
They died young, right?

00:06:16.310 --> 00:06:19.981
A little after they married, Maddie found out
Dash had been cheating on her from day one,

00:06:20.147 --> 00:06:23.427
and in a fit of heartbreak, she took her
own life with an overdose of secobarbital.

00:06:23.517 --> 00:06:27.387
Then, a few months later, on Halloween,

00:06:27.521 --> 00:06:31.726
Dash fell from that balcony
and broke his neck.

00:06:33.828 --> 00:06:37.164
Which is called a coincidence.
Police ruled the death accidental.

00:06:37.298 --> 00:06:39.667
Yes, but the ghost story crowd

00:06:39.800 --> 00:06:42.303
always said Maddie's ghost
pushed Dash over the rail,

00:06:42.402 --> 00:06:45.072
- and she still haunts the house today.
- Ooh.

00:06:45.206 --> 00:06:46.850
Look, I am not saying I believe that, but...

00:06:46.874 --> 00:06:49.377
Good. Because a ghost definitely
did not kill Danny Sternblatt.

00:06:49.510 --> 00:06:52.513
We have two options. It's
either murder or natural causes.

00:06:52.680 --> 00:06:53.681
[phone buzzes]

00:06:54.682 --> 00:06:56.817
- Lieutenant.
- [Selena] I'm sending you a text.

00:06:56.918 --> 00:06:59.520
The kids who called 911
sat with our sketch artist.

00:06:59.654 --> 00:07:01.322
Curious to hear your take.

00:07:03.190 --> 00:07:04.992
- What? What is it?
- [Karadec sighs]

00:07:09.196 --> 00:07:11.699
Sorry, you were just saying...

00:07:22.576 --> 00:07:23.878
[Daphne] Oh, wow.

00:07:24.011 --> 00:07:26.547
They even nailed the scalloped
lace on Maddie's veil.

00:07:26.681 --> 00:07:27.782
[Oz laughs]

00:07:27.915 --> 00:07:29.717
Fine, then you explain it.
What did they see?

00:07:29.884 --> 00:07:32.452
That photo, Daph. You found it online.

00:07:32.586 --> 00:07:34.889
They could've too.
It's a Halloween prank.

00:07:35.022 --> 00:07:36.934
They did say they came to the
house because of its history.

00:07:36.958 --> 00:07:39.226
Verbena, it's calming.

00:07:39.360 --> 00:07:40.895
[phone buzzing]

00:07:41.062 --> 00:07:44.398
ME's prelim is in. Danny
Sternblatt died of a heart attack.

00:07:44.565 --> 00:07:46.466
It wasn't his first.
He had one a few years ago.

00:07:46.600 --> 00:07:48.936
So unless we have something
that proves otherwise,

00:07:49.070 --> 00:07:50.738
they're gonna rule natural causes.

00:07:52.440 --> 00:07:53.473
Anyone else feel that?

00:07:54.442 --> 00:07:56.143
No? Weird.

00:07:56.277 --> 00:07:58.612
[inhales sharply, sighs]

00:07:59.479 --> 00:08:01.582
[crunching]

00:08:04.251 --> 00:08:05.453
Is this salt?

00:08:08.622 --> 00:08:12.793
Oh, oh. We might wanna pump
the brakes on the natural causes.

00:08:12.927 --> 00:08:15.096
- [Karadec] Because...
- Because Oz is right.

00:08:15.262 --> 00:08:19.000
At first, I thought it was just
plaster dust, but it's not. It's salt.

00:08:19.133 --> 00:08:25.439
Yeah, look, the salt leads to
fluorite, carnelian, labradorite,

00:08:25.606 --> 00:08:29.310
obsidian, and
I'm thinking... smoky quartz.

00:08:29.443 --> 00:08:32.947
Five stones connected by salt.
Danny made a pentacle.

00:08:33.114 --> 00:08:37.118
It's a symbol of protection in some
cultures, and so is that bracelet.

00:08:37.952 --> 00:08:41.122
Detective Karadec might not
believe in ghosts, but our victim did.

00:08:41.288 --> 00:08:43.424
Danny thought his house was haunted.

00:08:43.524 --> 00:08:44.692
[Danny screaming]

00:08:44.825 --> 00:08:46.603
[Morgan] He was
hearing and seeing crazy things

00:08:46.627 --> 00:08:48.796
he couldn't pinpoint,
so he trashed this entire place

00:08:48.929 --> 00:08:50.729
trying to figure out
where it was coming from.

00:08:52.133 --> 00:08:56.037
Guy had electricians, pest control,
plumbers, everyone checked this place out.

00:08:56.170 --> 00:08:59.173
Okay, Danny was hearing things
that go bump in the night,

00:08:59.306 --> 00:09:00.674
but we know it wasn't a ghost.

00:09:00.808 --> 00:09:03.144
I think somebody
who knew Danny had a bad heart,

00:09:03.277 --> 00:09:04.979
staged a haunting to scare him to death.

00:09:05.813 --> 00:09:06.981
That would be murder.

00:09:07.114 --> 00:09:08.883
All this witchy stuff is not Danny's style.

00:09:09.016 --> 00:09:10.851
Somebody had to help him set it up.

00:09:10.985 --> 00:09:13.387
And someone who could stop a
haunt might be able to fake one.

00:09:13.522 --> 00:09:15.356
Danny's phone is password-protected.

00:09:15.489 --> 00:09:17.324
It's gonna take TID some time to crack it.

00:09:17.491 --> 00:09:22.163
Oz, any of those invoices over there have
something to do with ghost remediation?

00:09:22.329 --> 00:09:23.798
- [Oz] Um...
- [papers rustle]

00:09:25.800 --> 00:09:28.736
No. But there is this.

00:09:33.508 --> 00:09:35.619
[Karadec] And just for my file,
the full name is Calliope...

00:09:35.643 --> 00:09:36.811
[Calliope] Just Calliope.

00:09:37.344 --> 00:09:39.080
I knew something felt off today.

00:09:40.181 --> 00:09:42.192
What was the nature of your
relationship with Mr. Sternblatt?

00:09:42.216 --> 00:09:44.185
Verbena? It's good for stress.

00:09:44.351 --> 00:09:47.254
Oh, thank you. We got our fill
at the crime scene.

00:09:48.022 --> 00:09:49.890
I was Danny's spiritual advisor.

00:09:50.024 --> 00:09:53.227
He was raised in a traditional faith
and never really connected with it.

00:09:53.360 --> 00:09:57.598
So when he reached a crossroads in
life, he preferred to ask the universe.

00:09:57.731 --> 00:09:59.233
Spiritual, not religious.

00:09:59.366 --> 00:10:00.734
Would you mind?

00:10:00.868 --> 00:10:03.871
We did a very difficult reading
for a client this morning.

00:10:04.004 --> 00:10:05.372
We need time to ground.

00:10:06.373 --> 00:10:08.676
What sort of crossroads
did you talk about with Danny?

00:10:08.776 --> 00:10:12.713
Business, mostly. Managing his
law firm, sometimes investments.

00:10:12.847 --> 00:10:14.583
Investments like buying
the Spencer house?

00:10:14.715 --> 00:10:16.315
[Calliope] Especially the Spencer house.

00:10:16.383 --> 00:10:18.986
He wouldn't sleep there until
I performed a clearing ritual,

00:10:19.120 --> 00:10:21.956
but it was his wife's dream
of dream houses.

00:10:22.089 --> 00:10:24.258
Sadly, the work I performed
there didn't last.

00:10:24.391 --> 00:10:26.794
After Lorraine left,
something dark welled up.

00:10:26.927 --> 00:10:30.297
So you're the one who helped him set
up all those protective elements, right?

00:10:30.431 --> 00:10:32.633
- Have you been in the house?
- Mm-hmm.

00:10:32.766 --> 00:10:36.605
So you felt the cold spot in the
basement? Heard the crying woman?

00:10:36.737 --> 00:10:38.939
- Mmm.
- Can't say that we have. Where was this?

00:10:39.073 --> 00:10:41.576
In the butler's pantry.
Well, that's where I heard her.

00:10:41.742 --> 00:10:44.912
Danny heard her at the same time
in the sitting room across the house.

00:10:45.045 --> 00:10:47.448
The energy in that place is very off.

00:10:47.582 --> 00:10:50.651
Yeah. Hey, how much do each
of these clearing rituals cost?

00:10:50.784 --> 00:10:52.119
Around 5,000.

00:10:52.253 --> 00:10:54.255
- Dollars?
- Yes. Why?

00:10:54.421 --> 00:10:55.990
Uh... I need a minute to ground.

00:10:56.123 --> 00:10:58.792
What my partner's saying is it
seems you caught yourself a whale.

00:10:58.926 --> 00:11:01.495
Danny was terrified and
more than willing to shell out.

00:11:01.630 --> 00:11:03.550
[chuckles] - Yeah, and
these rituals didn't work,

00:11:03.598 --> 00:11:05.332
but you knew that, didn't you?

00:11:05.466 --> 00:11:09.670
This green candle over here, you got
it just drenched in bergamot and myrtle.

00:11:09.803 --> 00:11:11.672
That's an abundance spell, right?

00:11:11.805 --> 00:11:14.108
Only typically those are done
during a waxing moon,

00:11:14.241 --> 00:11:15.610
and right now the moon's waning.

00:11:15.776 --> 00:11:17.111
You know your stuff.

00:11:20.447 --> 00:11:23.184
Ah. My cleaning lady
must have flipped that.

00:11:23.317 --> 00:11:26.453
Oh. Yeah. Yeah,
I think I do know my stuff.

00:11:26.555 --> 00:11:30.625
I also know that a woman who refers
to herself and her tarot deck as "we,"

00:11:30.758 --> 00:11:34.663
doesn't need to consult a calendar
to find out the moon phases.

00:11:34.795 --> 00:11:36.631
- You calling me a fraud?
- I am.

00:11:36.797 --> 00:11:38.108
[Karadec] So, Calliope, what happened?

00:11:38.132 --> 00:11:39.534
Did Danny catch on to your scam?

00:11:39.668 --> 00:11:41.278
Cut off the funds,
so you scared him to death?

00:11:41.302 --> 00:11:42.970
[chuckles] No, why would I do that?

00:11:43.137 --> 00:11:46.140
My entire business would collapse if
people found out my clients were dying.

00:11:46.307 --> 00:11:47.841
Now, unless I am under arrest,

00:11:47.975 --> 00:11:50.444
please leave and take your
closed hearts with you.

00:11:50.545 --> 00:11:52.112
This is a sacred space.

00:11:52.213 --> 00:11:54.181
This is a bungalow in El Segundo.

00:11:54.315 --> 00:11:55.684
Morgan, let's go.

00:11:55.816 --> 00:11:58.352
If you don't believe the
Spencer house is haunted, fine.

00:11:58.485 --> 00:12:00.187
But the things I told you did happen,

00:12:00.321 --> 00:12:04.659
so perhaps focus less on me
and look into what caused them.

00:12:12.299 --> 00:12:13.801
What? She put me in a bad mood.

00:12:13.901 --> 00:12:16.170
- When were you in a good mood?
- I'm a delight.

00:12:16.337 --> 00:12:18.348
Well, fraud or no fraud,
Calliope made a good point.

00:12:18.372 --> 00:12:20.572
It wasn't in her best interest
to kill her golden goose.

00:12:20.675 --> 00:12:22.052
And she gave us specifics we can use.

00:12:22.076 --> 00:12:24.679
A cold spot in the basement,
a woman crying.

00:12:24.845 --> 00:12:27.014
Someone planted those scares
to freak Sternblatt out.

00:12:27.181 --> 00:12:28.781
And maybe they left
some evidence behind.

00:12:30.518 --> 00:12:31.553
[crow caws]

00:12:32.554 --> 00:12:34.689
[clock ticks]

00:12:42.196 --> 00:12:43.230
[clattering]

00:12:48.869 --> 00:12:50.237
[loud thud]

00:12:56.210 --> 00:12:57.746
[rattling in distance]

00:13:02.950 --> 00:13:04.619
[rustling]

00:13:05.687 --> 00:13:07.288
[clattering]

00:13:07.421 --> 00:13:09.957
[squeaking]

00:13:24.606 --> 00:13:27.408
- [phone buzzing]
- [sighs]

00:13:29.109 --> 00:13:31.879
- Yeah?
- Hey, how's it going down there?

00:13:31.979 --> 00:13:34.582
Uh, great. If you like spiders.

00:13:35.717 --> 00:13:38.787
Otherwise, not much to report. You?

00:13:38.952 --> 00:13:41.155
Just a rat, cute little guy or gal.

00:13:41.288 --> 00:13:43.924
Not a lot of differentiating characteristics.

00:13:47.629 --> 00:13:48.929
Morgan?

00:13:49.096 --> 00:13:52.634
Calliope said
that they heard a woman crying

00:13:52.767 --> 00:13:54.803
in two different parts of the house, right?

00:13:55.603 --> 00:14:01.108
Well, my kids used to talk to each
other through the vents in their bedrooms.

00:14:03.645 --> 00:14:05.346
Oh, hello.

00:14:38.780 --> 00:14:40.180
- Morgan?
- Mm-hmm.

00:14:40.314 --> 00:14:41.834
I think you're gonna want to see this.

00:14:56.163 --> 00:14:57.164
Morgan, where are you?

00:14:57.331 --> 00:14:58.733
What's going on? Just tell me.

00:14:59.233 --> 00:15:00.502
Someone,

00:15:01.001 --> 00:15:02.336
or something.

00:15:02.504 --> 00:15:04.739
LAPD, put your hands
where I can see 'em.

00:15:06.340 --> 00:15:07.408
We got another runner.

00:15:07.542 --> 00:15:09.009
[♪ "Go Dumb" playing]

00:15:09.176 --> 00:15:11.011
♪ I go forty down to fifty ♪

00:15:12.212 --> 00:15:14.716
♪ I can rise With the
tide... ♪ - [Morgan shrieks]

00:15:15.983 --> 00:15:18.419
- Get-Get off!
- [grunting]

00:15:18.553 --> 00:15:21.823
- Not what I was expecting.
- Yeah, me neither. Get off me.

00:15:21.922 --> 00:15:23.525
- [grunts]
- [Karadec] Get up.

00:15:24.358 --> 00:15:26.798
[intruder grunting] -On your
feet. On your feet. On your feet.

00:15:27.261 --> 00:15:29.597
- Let me go. I didn't do anything.
- All right.

00:15:29.731 --> 00:15:32.366
Found this in a vent. Let's see.

00:15:32.534 --> 00:15:35.904
Okay, a couple of iPads,
some computer stuff,

00:15:36.036 --> 00:15:37.739
just standard things

00:15:37.872 --> 00:15:39.850
that somebody hiding in a basement
wearing a wedding dress would have.

00:15:39.874 --> 00:15:42.514
- I'm guessing these are yours.
- Come on. Let's go to the station.

00:15:42.544 --> 00:15:44.522
You can tell me more about
how you weren't doing anything.

00:15:44.546 --> 00:15:45.780
Easy. Easy.

00:15:52.085 --> 00:15:56.256
[sighing] Oh, thank goodness. I'd hate
to think anybody was getting any sunlight.

00:15:56.390 --> 00:15:58.258
I've been outside. Wasn't impressed.

00:15:58.893 --> 00:16:00.528
- How was work?
- Pretty good.

00:16:00.628 --> 00:16:05.232
I helped stop a fleeing suspect
today, mostly by just standing there,

00:16:05.399 --> 00:16:06.967
but still, the job got done.

00:16:07.100 --> 00:16:09.537
She's being questioned
right now, so I had a little time.

00:16:09.637 --> 00:16:12.807
I thought I'd come home and get
dinner started before Ludo gets here,

00:16:12.941 --> 00:16:14.241
then I gotta head back.

00:16:14.374 --> 00:16:16.443
How were your days?
Chloe go down for her nap okay?

00:16:17.579 --> 00:16:21.248
Uh, yeah, Ava got Chloe down,
no problem. School was the usual.

00:16:21.381 --> 00:16:24.786
I'm pretty sure Mr. Cabral doesn't know
the difference between mass and weight,

00:16:24.919 --> 00:16:26.730
but don't worry,
I pulled him aside after class.

00:16:26.754 --> 00:16:28.489
Mmm. I bet he loved that.

00:16:29.456 --> 00:16:31.559
So what do you think?
Burritos okay for dinner?

00:16:33.928 --> 00:16:35.128
We're still doing this, huh?

00:16:37.464 --> 00:16:42.604
Ava was invited to a Halloween party
this weekend, and she really wants to go,

00:16:42.737 --> 00:16:45.807
but I think she's still upset
that she's grounded.

00:16:46.608 --> 00:16:47.775
Really?

00:16:47.909 --> 00:16:50.277
You think it might be
a smart idea to apologize

00:16:50.444 --> 00:16:53.915
for blatantly disobeying me first,
and then we could go from there?

00:16:54.014 --> 00:16:56.250
[huffs] - Ava thinks she
didn't do anything wrong.

00:16:56.350 --> 00:16:58.686
Babe, it's not your job to fix this, okay?

00:16:59.319 --> 00:17:01.998
We're all right. Why don't you go do
something that doesn't involve a screen?

00:17:02.022 --> 00:17:03.123
Okay.

00:17:09.463 --> 00:17:12.199
Ava, how long do you
want to play this game?

00:17:12.332 --> 00:17:15.003
Mom, it's been a week. This is so unfair.

00:17:16.804 --> 00:17:17.804
[door slams]

00:17:17.839 --> 00:17:20.374
Children are such a blessing.

00:17:29.651 --> 00:17:31.553
Captain Wagner, a word.

00:17:31.686 --> 00:17:34.154
Anytime. This case is a weird one, huh?

00:17:34.288 --> 00:17:35.957
It is.

00:17:36.056 --> 00:17:38.434
It's not every day a captain insists
on questioning a suspect himself.

00:17:38.458 --> 00:17:40.962
Oh, come on. Woman
in an antique wedding dress

00:17:41.061 --> 00:17:43.497
pretending to be a ghost
to scare a man to death.

00:17:43.665 --> 00:17:45.465
How often do one of those come along?

00:17:46.199 --> 00:17:49.037
The mayor's a family friend.
Wants updates.

00:17:49.169 --> 00:17:52.040
Pretty sure he and half his golf
buddies want this case closed

00:17:52.172 --> 00:17:54.241
before Sternblatt's law practice

00:17:54.374 --> 00:17:57.477
and all their divorce details
get dragged through the mud.

00:17:57.579 --> 00:17:59.246
- I see.
- Shouldn't affect you, though.

00:17:59.379 --> 00:18:02.550
I provide cover. You work
the case, long as it takes.

00:18:02.684 --> 00:18:04.084
That's a nice sentiment,

00:18:04.217 --> 00:18:06.588
only I just got off the phone
with the Department of Media.

00:18:06.721 --> 00:18:09.524
They were fact-checking a
press release about the arrest,

00:18:09.657 --> 00:18:11.425
the one I assume
you're holding right now.

00:18:12.026 --> 00:18:13.871
Rushing this out when
we don't have the facts yet

00:18:13.895 --> 00:18:16.731
doesn't seem to me like
letting the wheels of justice turn.

00:18:17.865 --> 00:18:20.735
This arrest, sloppy police work?

00:18:20.868 --> 00:18:23.037
No, she's our haunter.

00:18:23.538 --> 00:18:25.039
Then you have nothing to worry about.

00:18:30.110 --> 00:18:31.679
- [sighs]
- [door closes]

00:18:32.947 --> 00:18:34.716
[Nick] Shawna Khurmi.

00:18:35.717 --> 00:18:36.718
That's K-H-U...

00:18:40.253 --> 00:18:41.623
Is the furniture small?

00:18:41.756 --> 00:18:43.256
No, you're big.

00:18:45.593 --> 00:18:49.097
Guess the world wasn't built
for people my size, huh?

00:18:50.098 --> 00:18:53.901
Anyway, it's Khurmi.
K-H-U-R-M-I. Twenty-seven.

00:18:54.035 --> 00:18:57.471
Special effects wiz.
Electrical engineering. Oh.

00:18:58.238 --> 00:18:59.807
Cal Arts grad. Wow.

00:18:59.941 --> 00:19:03.310
- I've asked for a lawyer.
- Yes, I heard, as is your right.

00:19:03.443 --> 00:19:06.948
It's just that this release is
gonna go out before they get here,

00:19:07.081 --> 00:19:09.059
so I thought I'd give you
a chance to correct the error.

00:19:09.083 --> 00:19:10.918
So it is true.
New cap's doing the interview.

00:19:11.052 --> 00:19:12.086
Mm-hmm.

00:19:12.252 --> 00:19:13.721
Mind if I watch?

00:19:15.255 --> 00:19:16.958
Knock yourself out.

00:19:17.091 --> 00:19:21.596
You know, I won't lie. Lawyers hate
these releases. Court of public opinion.

00:19:21.729 --> 00:19:25.800
Once we tell the world you're a killer,
good luck convincing a jury otherwise.

00:19:25.933 --> 00:19:28.002
But we're just gonna go
with what we know.

00:19:28.136 --> 00:19:30.303
You applied your skills
to stage a high-tech haunt

00:19:30.437 --> 00:19:31.572
spanning a matter of months.

00:19:31.673 --> 00:19:33.173
You used your fancy toys

00:19:33.306 --> 00:19:37.779
and an inspired cameo as
the ghost of Maddie St. Croix

00:19:37.912 --> 00:19:39.479
that led to the death of Danny.

00:19:40.081 --> 00:19:42.984
You killed him. And then you
saw those kids at the window.

00:19:43.117 --> 00:19:44.757
You knew the cops
were coming then, right?

00:19:44.852 --> 00:19:46.521
At least that's the story now.

00:19:48.355 --> 00:19:50.925
But you know, I know you have
a lot of student debt,

00:19:51.025 --> 00:19:55.129
and I also can't tie you to Sternblatt,
which means someone paid you.

00:19:55.663 --> 00:19:56.998
Shawna, give me their name,

00:19:57.799 --> 00:19:59.967
and this press release disappears.

00:20:00.635 --> 00:20:02.103
You don't get labeled a killer

00:20:02.202 --> 00:20:04.772
and this whole thing
comes grinding to a halt.

00:20:04.872 --> 00:20:06.174
[Oz chuckles]

00:20:07.809 --> 00:20:09.010
Help me help you.

00:20:11.512 --> 00:20:13.123
I tried to save him, but I don't know CPR,

00:20:13.147 --> 00:20:14.792
and she never told me
about his heart condition.

00:20:14.816 --> 00:20:16.150
She who?

00:20:16.316 --> 00:20:17.852
Danny's wife, Lorraine.

00:20:22.355 --> 00:20:23.825
Wow, that's, uh

00:20:24.491 --> 00:20:27.227
[clears throat] that's good. It's good work.

00:20:27.360 --> 00:20:28.863
Sure, but he still could've told us.

00:20:29.997 --> 00:20:32.142
- Lorraine back in town yet?
- She should've just landed.

00:20:32.166 --> 00:20:34.478
She did say something about
having to stop by her office first

00:20:34.502 --> 00:20:35.636
before coming to see us.

00:20:35.737 --> 00:20:37.457
Then have Karadec and Morgan
meet her there.

00:20:37.538 --> 00:20:39.073
I think she'll squeeze us in.

00:20:43.544 --> 00:20:45.689
[person] I'm just trying to
make sure you're taken care of.

00:20:45.713 --> 00:20:49.650
No, you're not. You're trying to
make sure you're taken care of.

00:20:49.751 --> 00:20:52.186
You always loved that house
more than you loved my dad.

00:20:55.489 --> 00:20:58.258
Excuse me. LAPD.

00:20:59.527 --> 00:21:01.896
Did you just say
Danny Sternblatt was your dad?

00:21:02.029 --> 00:21:04.098
Yeah, I'm Paloma Nichols.

00:21:04.232 --> 00:21:05.533
I'm really sorry for your loss.

00:21:05.700 --> 00:21:07.544
It doesn't sound like Lorraine
in there is your mom?

00:21:07.568 --> 00:21:10.705
[scoffs] Dad's second wife.
He and my mom split ages ago.

00:21:11.706 --> 00:21:14.242
Wait, do you think Lorraine had
something to do with his death?

00:21:14.374 --> 00:21:15.877
It's too soon to comment.

00:21:16.010 --> 00:21:18.411
[sighs] I wouldn't put it past her.

00:21:18.546 --> 00:21:21.682
She invited me here
to supposedly make peace.

00:21:22.216 --> 00:21:24.018
Really, she wanted
to feel out my intentions.

00:21:24.118 --> 00:21:25.887
My dad's body isn't even cold yet.

00:21:26.754 --> 00:21:29.557
Uh, sorry, Ms. Nichols, we may
have some questions for you too.

00:21:29.724 --> 00:21:32.392
- Is there any way we can reach you?
- Yeah.

00:21:32.527 --> 00:21:35.263
It's Dr. Nichols. Here's all my info.

00:21:36.264 --> 00:21:38.431
When you are ready to comment,
I'd love to hear it.

00:21:38.566 --> 00:21:41.468
[Lorraine] Jody, I'm wiped.
I'm gonna head home.

00:21:41.602 --> 00:21:43.638
Hey, if the, uh, police call again,

00:21:43.771 --> 00:21:46.073
let them know
I'll go there in the morning.

00:21:47.074 --> 00:21:48.242
Saved you the trip.

00:21:50.244 --> 00:21:52.613
Ms. Khurmi identified you by name.

00:21:52.747 --> 00:21:54.627
Says you met when you spoke
at a class she took,

00:21:54.749 --> 00:21:57.652
and a few months later, you
approached her for help with a haunting

00:21:57.785 --> 00:22:00.021
and offered her a job
at your firm in exchange.

00:22:00.154 --> 00:22:03.257
Shawna says she had no idea about
Danny's heart, and we believe her.

00:22:03.390 --> 00:22:05.293
The problem is you did know,

00:22:05.425 --> 00:22:08.105
because he'd had a previous heart
attack when you guys were married.

00:22:09.263 --> 00:22:10.463
I knew.

00:22:11.766 --> 00:22:13.301
His recovery was the last time

00:22:13.433 --> 00:22:15.803
I can remember us being good
to each other.

00:22:16.771 --> 00:22:19.173
So it sounds like you did
love each other at one point.

00:22:19.307 --> 00:22:20.908
Yeah, I mean, I...

00:22:22.677 --> 00:22:26.080
He used to write me
these letters all the time.

00:22:27.849 --> 00:22:32.620
We were one of history's great
couples, like Dash and Maddie.

00:22:33.254 --> 00:22:36.524
Until Danny started acting a little too
much like Dash and cheated on you.

00:22:36.657 --> 00:22:37.992
I was devastated.

00:22:39.627 --> 00:22:44.699
And then when I decided that I had
enough, he used every trick against me.

00:22:44.832 --> 00:22:48.669
He changed locks while I was
traveling, swore I'd never get the house.

00:22:49.303 --> 00:22:51.205
It was all about winning.

00:22:51.339 --> 00:22:54.484
So you decided to play dirty too and used
his superstitions to get what you wanted.

00:22:54.508 --> 00:22:56.878
[sighs] Listen, I know that it went too far,

00:22:57.678 --> 00:23:00.181
but I never wanted to kill him.

00:23:00.314 --> 00:23:01.682
I just wanted the house.

00:23:02.350 --> 00:23:05.720
I mean, I figured if I spooked him
enough, he would just sign it over.

00:23:07.487 --> 00:23:11.659
Wait, you met his daughter
on her way out.

00:23:11.826 --> 00:23:15.329
The house was in Danny's name.
He... He left it to her.

00:23:15.495 --> 00:23:16.831
She would inherit the house.

00:23:16.964 --> 00:23:20.034
You needed him to give it over
to you while he was alive.

00:23:21.202 --> 00:23:22.402
Yeah, well...

00:23:23.170 --> 00:23:27.208
Doesn't change the fact that he's
dead and I have to live with that.

00:23:30.378 --> 00:23:32.914
Wait, is this Danny's handwriting?

00:23:33.480 --> 00:23:35.880
Oh, this doesn't look anything
like the letters at the house.

00:23:37.484 --> 00:23:41.355
That writing was really messy,
shaky, like his hands were weak.

00:23:41.522 --> 00:23:44.025
Also, I think he was off-balance.

00:23:44.725 --> 00:23:47.161
Poor guy was stumbling all
over the place like the undead.

00:23:47.828 --> 00:23:50.031
Karadec, I think we've gotta
check those sleeping pills.

00:23:50.197 --> 00:23:51.917
I'll have the ME fast-track his tox report.

00:23:52.033 --> 00:23:53.701
[stutters] Wait, what's going on?

00:23:54.568 --> 00:23:57.605
You could have scared Danny
to death, but I don't think you did.

00:24:00.241 --> 00:24:01.542
I think he was poisoned.

00:24:04.578 --> 00:24:06.213
Lab reports are back.

00:24:07.014 --> 00:24:08.382
Those weren't sleeping pills.

00:24:08.549 --> 00:24:11.953
Danny Sternblatt died from
a potassium chloride overdose

00:24:12.086 --> 00:24:13.955
which induced a fatal heart attack.

00:24:14.088 --> 00:24:15.768
ME said it was a smart way
to kill someone.

00:24:15.890 --> 00:24:18.893
Potassium chloride spikes
naturally in the blood after death.

00:24:19.026 --> 00:24:20.337
Autopsy never would've caught it.

00:24:20.361 --> 00:24:22.296
Which means if we
hadn't tested those pills,

00:24:22.430 --> 00:24:25.190
Lorraine Sternblatt would've gone
down for a murder she didn't commit.

00:24:25.232 --> 00:24:26.767
Solid catch by Morgan.

00:24:26.901 --> 00:24:29.741
So, someone knew the wife was
gaslighting Danny and piggybacked on that,

00:24:29.770 --> 00:24:32.273
making it look
like she haunted him to death.

00:24:32.406 --> 00:24:34.141
- Who?
- Had to be someone close to him,

00:24:34.275 --> 00:24:35.595
someone with access to the pills.

00:24:35.710 --> 00:24:37.187
You take a closer look at the daughter?

00:24:37.211 --> 00:24:39.389
Paloma will get the house, but
the money motive feels weak.

00:24:39.413 --> 00:24:42.125
I mean, she's an orthopedic surgeon
married to another orthopedic surgeon.

00:24:42.149 --> 00:24:43.417
She's fine.

00:24:44.085 --> 00:24:47.254
What about Sternblatt's practice?
Didn't the wife say he was tough as nails?

00:24:47.355 --> 00:24:49.275
Yeah, said he used
every nasty trick in the book.

00:24:49.390 --> 00:24:50.670
Even came up with some new ones.

00:24:50.791 --> 00:24:53.260
Maybe a divorcé he did
a number on wanted revenge?

00:24:53.427 --> 00:24:55.507
Or maybe a rival lawyer.
We'll head over to his firm.

00:24:55.563 --> 00:24:57.598
If the guy had enemies
over there, we'll find out.

00:24:59.333 --> 00:25:00.935
- He was murdered?
- Mmm.

00:25:01.102 --> 00:25:03.971
Oh, my God. I figured
his heart just gave out.

00:25:04.105 --> 00:25:08.009
Were you aware Mr. Sternblatt
thought that his house was, um, haunted?

00:25:08.743 --> 00:25:10.511
He made it impossible not to know.

00:25:11.112 --> 00:25:15.082
Danny was freaking everyone out, that
woo-woo bracelet, jumping at shadows.

00:25:15.182 --> 00:25:17.485
We're wondering if anyone he
went up against with in court

00:25:17.618 --> 00:25:19.763
might've known that too and
used that knowledge against him.

00:25:19.787 --> 00:25:21.522
[scoffs] I wish.

00:25:22.323 --> 00:25:24.525
Well, I'm sorry.
[stammers] That came out wrong.

00:25:24.658 --> 00:25:27.495
I just meant that Danny wasn't
in court anytime recently.

00:25:27.628 --> 00:25:31.132
He was too wrapped up in his own
divorce and winning that damn house.

00:25:31.298 --> 00:25:33.010
He handed off all his other
cases months ago,

00:25:33.034 --> 00:25:35.202
stopped coming in at all
the last few weeks.

00:25:37.004 --> 00:25:38.639
Look, I was worried about my friend.

00:25:44.678 --> 00:25:45.679
Wouldn't you be?

00:25:46.680 --> 00:25:48.482
Have at it. I have to call my wife.

00:25:52.620 --> 00:25:56.157
Huh. Well, sounds like Sternblatt
wasn't making any enemies here.

00:25:56.323 --> 00:25:58.492
- Took himself completely off the board.
- Mm-hmm.

00:25:59.226 --> 00:26:01.629
Feels like all roads keep leading
back to the Spencer house.

00:26:02.997 --> 00:26:05.277
What do you say we give
Daphne's ghost theory another run?

00:26:06.801 --> 00:26:08.402
I just do not get this guy.

00:26:08.537 --> 00:26:10.838
I mean, digging in
out of spite, that's one thing,

00:26:11.005 --> 00:26:13.007
but Sternblatt hated the house.

00:26:13.140 --> 00:26:15.209
He wasn't sleeping.
He knew he had a bad heart.

00:26:15.342 --> 00:26:17.988
At a certain point, you would think,
that the fear of having a heart attack

00:26:18.012 --> 00:26:19.713
would override the desire
to win a divorce.

00:26:19.847 --> 00:26:21.415
[phone buzzing]

00:26:22.883 --> 00:26:24.685
You're missing out, Gillory.

00:26:24.819 --> 00:26:27.859
It looks like one of your crime boards
exploded all over our victim's office.

00:26:28.022 --> 00:26:31.158
Only in every direction it's
nothing but house, house, house.

00:26:31.258 --> 00:26:33.494
- Maybe it is something.
- [Oz] What's that?

00:26:33.594 --> 00:26:37.064
Well, I was doing a little digging around
in the Sternblatt divorce documents

00:26:37.198 --> 00:26:40.267
trying to find something that would
pop out as a motive to kill Danny.

00:26:40.401 --> 00:26:41.669
- And?
- Nothing popped.

00:26:41.769 --> 00:26:43.647
But then I noticed something
weird about the house.

00:26:43.671 --> 00:26:47.576
The appraisal when they bought it
showed it as 300 square feet smaller

00:26:47.708 --> 00:26:50.579
than it was when it was
appraised in the 1940s.

00:26:50.711 --> 00:26:52.222
I mean, maybe that's a mistake, but...

00:26:52.246 --> 00:26:55.449
No. No, it's here on the blueprints too.

00:26:55.584 --> 00:27:02.022
300-square-foot difference
between the old and the new.

00:27:02.123 --> 00:27:06.427
How could they lose 300 square feet,
but the footprints look exactly the same?

00:27:06.561 --> 00:27:08.629
- It's like there's a...
- Disappearing room?

00:27:08.762 --> 00:27:10.565
I don't think we're done there yet, boys.

00:27:10.698 --> 00:27:13.400
I think the Spencer house has
more secrets to tell.

00:27:13.535 --> 00:27:16.470
And I'm sensing you have
a way of figuring that out?

00:27:29.618 --> 00:27:31.318
He didn't need to straighten that.

00:27:31.452 --> 00:27:34.355
Mind if I ask why you pulled
half my bullpen down here?

00:27:34.488 --> 00:27:36.824
Do you mind if I answer
in the form of a story?

00:27:36.957 --> 00:27:38.969
Don't answer that. It's
happening. It's starting right now.

00:27:38.993 --> 00:27:43.330
Deep in the gloomy glens of ancient
Scotland stands Castle Glamis.

00:27:43.464 --> 00:27:46.934
Legend has it that the heir
of the 11th Earl of Strathmore

00:27:47.101 --> 00:27:50.804
was hidden away in a secret room that
was walled up, never to be seen again.

00:27:50.938 --> 00:27:55.009
But then, a few hundred years later,
there was a new lady of the castle,

00:27:55.142 --> 00:27:57.978
and she set out to find
the infamous hidden chamber.

00:27:58.112 --> 00:28:01.782
This Lady Glamis knew that if a
room had actually been walled up

00:28:01.916 --> 00:28:03.276
that it would still have a window.

00:28:03.317 --> 00:28:04.852
So she asked her ladies-in-waiting

00:28:04.985 --> 00:28:07.488
to tie a handkerchief to
every window they could find.

00:28:08.489 --> 00:28:10.191
And lo and behold,

00:28:10.324 --> 00:28:13.961
only one window remained that
was hanky-free from the outside.

00:28:14.128 --> 00:28:17.031
And that was
how she found the secret room.

00:28:18.332 --> 00:28:19.934
And there it is.

00:28:22.836 --> 00:28:25.139
I'm guessing
this was Lorraine's craft room

00:28:25.306 --> 00:28:26.807
before Danny booted her out.

00:28:27.474 --> 00:28:30.311
Okay, that secret room's gotta
be behind these bookshelves.

00:28:31.278 --> 00:28:32.479
Oh!

00:28:32.947 --> 00:28:35.216
- You see it?
- Why don't you help us see it?

00:28:35.349 --> 00:28:37.519
This panel, it's plain sawn.

00:28:37.652 --> 00:28:39.386
It has to do with how they cut the lumber.

00:28:39.521 --> 00:28:41.965
These shelves are all quarter
sawn, so is the rest of the house,

00:28:41.989 --> 00:28:44.358
but this panel is plain sawn.

00:28:44.491 --> 00:28:46.994
Maybe Danny broke that panel
when he was tearing this place up

00:28:47.161 --> 00:28:50.130
and then repaired it,
but why only make the one fix?

00:28:50.231 --> 00:28:51.298
[screaming]

00:29:10.017 --> 00:29:11.586
Mmm. Maybe to hide this?

00:29:16.691 --> 00:29:18.859
This is Maddie's old boudoir.

00:29:19.360 --> 00:29:22.429
Oh, and that hat, that's the
hat that she wore to the premiere

00:29:22.564 --> 00:29:24.398
of the last film she made with Dash.

00:29:24.532 --> 00:29:28.269
Can I try a couple of these things on
before they get shipped off to some museum?

00:29:28.402 --> 00:29:30.237
- They're evidence.
- I'll be careful.

00:29:30.371 --> 00:29:33.774
So we think this room's been
tucked away for 70-plus years?

00:29:33.907 --> 00:29:36.678
Well, Maddie took her own life.
Dash must have walled it up.

00:29:36.777 --> 00:29:39.055
Probably because his conscience
couldn't handle any reminders

00:29:39.079 --> 00:29:40.423
of the woman he'd driven to suicide.

00:29:40.447 --> 00:29:42.216
[Daphne] Check out this gem.

