Root beer on an unprotected
lip? You're a madman.

00:30:31.231 --> 00:30:33.267
- I'll take it slow.
- Did I shame you into that?

00:30:33.434 --> 00:30:34.968
No, no, it was time.

00:30:35.102 --> 00:30:36.782
All winning streaks
have to come to an end.

00:30:36.937 --> 00:30:38.305
Is that what we're calling it?

00:30:38.439 --> 00:30:39.774
It's okay. I'll take the can.

00:30:41.676 --> 00:30:43.812
Hey, you a Dash and Maddie fan?

00:30:44.478 --> 00:30:46.447
- Mmm.
- Yeah, I was.

00:30:46.614 --> 00:30:48.783
Little disappointed in all the gory details.

00:30:48.949 --> 00:30:51.820
Yeah, this case isn't a ringing
endorsement for marriage.

00:30:52.319 --> 00:30:53.487
Ever been?

00:30:53.621 --> 00:30:55.289
Married? No.

00:30:56.123 --> 00:31:00.595
No. No, I mean, weddings are
great. There's... It's very sweet.

00:31:00.695 --> 00:31:03.163
I get it. [Stammers] I just...

00:31:03.931 --> 00:31:07.968
It's good for people. I just... The whole
courthouse and the paperwork and the

00:31:09.103 --> 00:31:12.973
the permanence of it, you know,
kind of kills the romance.

00:31:18.312 --> 00:31:20.515
- Yeah?
- Oh, just seeing some things.

00:31:20.648 --> 00:31:21.816
I don't think you are.

00:31:21.982 --> 00:31:23.594
- If this was an interrogation...
- It's not though.

00:31:23.618 --> 00:31:25.338
It's not an interrogation, so knock it off.

00:31:25.452 --> 00:31:27.789
- Well, now I know I'm right.
- [laughs]

00:31:28.523 --> 00:31:32.226
Okay. Fine, what things are you seeing?

00:31:32.359 --> 00:31:34.529
Well, first of all, you're
gripping that can so tight,

00:31:34.662 --> 00:31:36.731
I'm worried you're going
to be wearing the soda.

00:31:37.532 --> 00:31:40.901
The neck massage, a little self
soothing, fiddling with the candy.

00:31:41.034 --> 00:31:44.071
Those eyes of yours are jumping
around to everywhere but mine.

00:31:44.204 --> 00:31:47.207
I think the talk of marriage is
making you a little anxious.

00:31:47.341 --> 00:31:48.543
- Okay.
- [chuckles]

00:31:48.676 --> 00:31:52.547
[titters] Yeah, yeah,
I don't like it, you know.

00:31:53.213 --> 00:31:58.385
My brain has a way of making
sure relationships don't last very long,

00:31:58.520 --> 00:32:00.087
so let's just leave it at that.

00:32:00.220 --> 00:32:02.389
- Okay.
- What about you?

00:32:02.524 --> 00:32:04.024
Me? Oh.

00:32:04.526 --> 00:32:07.361
I'm into a four-year deal
that's working out pretty well.

00:32:07.529 --> 00:32:09.029
- Really?
- Yeah.

00:32:09.163 --> 00:32:12.700
She understands me, and, for
the most part, I understand her.

00:32:14.569 --> 00:32:15.770
[Morgan chuckles]

00:32:16.571 --> 00:32:18.038
- She's gorgeous.
- Thanks.

00:32:18.205 --> 00:32:19.741
- She have a name?
- Ingrid.

00:32:19.874 --> 00:32:22.544
Well, congratulations.
Ingrid seems like a real catch.

00:32:22.710 --> 00:32:24.378
Thank you.

00:32:24.512 --> 00:32:26.490
What about an actual human woman?
Have you ever married one of those?

00:32:26.514 --> 00:32:27.549
[chuckles]

00:32:28.415 --> 00:32:29.551
Got real close.

00:32:31.218 --> 00:32:32.687
She passed away a few years ago.

00:32:34.789 --> 00:32:35.857
I'm sorry.

00:32:36.390 --> 00:32:37.792
Yeah, me too.

00:32:38.760 --> 00:32:40.427
[phone buzzes]

00:32:42.396 --> 00:32:44.532
Hmm. Looks like they need us.

00:32:49.637 --> 00:32:53.908
[Karadec] 18-karat white gold waterfall,
102 cushion antique cut diamonds,

00:32:54.041 --> 00:32:57.244
85 French cut for
a grand total of 317 carats.

00:32:57.745 --> 00:33:02.082
Designed in Paris by celebrated sisters
Ophelia and Josephine Beaumont in 1946.

00:33:02.249 --> 00:33:03.984
- It's a strong accent.
- Hmm.

00:33:04.117 --> 00:33:05.419
So it's authentic.

00:33:05.587 --> 00:33:08.121
According to our contact,
based on the piece itself,

00:33:08.288 --> 00:33:10.925
- she said it was worth around ten million.
- [scoffs]

00:33:11.091 --> 00:33:13.661
That and a sexy providence
with a tragic Hollywood ending

00:33:13.795 --> 00:33:15.763
- and you, what, double the price?
- [gasps]

00:33:15.930 --> 00:33:17.130
Sounds about right.

00:33:17.264 --> 00:33:18.475
[Nick] So why was it still there?

00:33:18.499 --> 00:33:20.167
Sternblatt must've ball parked its worth.

